        <p class="sectionTag">Experience serenity inspired by the land</p>
        <p class="sectionsubTag">
          Grand Forest Metsovo hotel lies on the slopes of the Pindus Mountain
          range – at the footsteps of Pindus National Park. An unrivalled
          location to experience the breathtaking views of the surrounding
          peaks, discover the elusive brown bear deep in the forest or explore
          the atmospheric old town of Metsovo.The national park has an elevation
          range from 1,076 to 2,177 metres (3,530 to 7,142 ft) and is
          characterized by dense forests of European black pine and common
          beech, rocky ridges, several peaks over 2,000 metres (6,600 ft), rapid
          streams and mountain lakes. The area belong to the wider Pindus
          Mountains mixed forests ecoregion and is a representative part of
          Pindus mountain range.Moreover, it belongs to the Natura 2000
          ecological network of protected areas and is one of the three places
          in Greece that hosts a population of brown bears.
        </p>
